never worked in finance or for a startup, you are totally obsessed with digital systems and building scalable layouts. You make a complex lot of elements easier to visually digest using scale, proximity, typography and your expert UX knowledge. You understand how difficult simple can be and strive for clarity. Strategic You\u2019re comfortable using your creativity in the grey areas as part of an agile yet empowered team. Merging a product marketing strategy, creative direction, and a myriad of content, you think deeply about the requirements and implementation, but you also know how to step back and see the broader impact of the system you create and its relationship to future versions. Productive You are driven to get things (well) done. You recognize when projects need more or less energy, and use opportunities to work smarter. You\u2019re a die-hard advocate for tidiness and efficiency using Sketch, essentially owning our design process and its improvement as we scale. Chops You have a stand-out portfolio that displays what you're capable of in web design and HubSpot web development. You\u2019re confident presenting your ideas with pitch decks, documentation, online and in-person. What you\u2019ll work on: Help architect UX flows and design a system of templates and components for a new Circle marketing website built on HubSpot, including product marketing pages, content pages, blog, emails, and other customer touchpoints Work to iteratively scale and maintain the Circle visual system, including our brand guide, pattern library, UI toolkits, and implementation guidelines Partner with your creative director and content creators to lead the implementation of site updates on the HubSpot platform, designing and building new web experiences as we grow, acting as the in-house design go-to with our developer contractors Design and web production work like engaging social & blog graphics, digital PDFs, infographics, data visualizations, and branded materials for investors, partners, corporate comms, talent, and Circle employees Support the business/product/marketing (BPM) team with creating quick-turn lead-gen landing pages, responsive emails, and Google Slides presentations Actively participate in creative problem solving across all brand and marketing initiatives and owned channels What you'll bring to Circle: 3+ years in a web design role either on or partnering with creative marketing team Working proficiency in HubL and experience building custom templates with HubSpot Mastery at Sketch (and sometimes Photoshop), including maintaining Sketch libraries and managing process Top-notch web typography, responsive design, and accessibility knowledge Experience prototyping with Invision and Craft Experience working with creative and non-creative partners to produce compelling layouts with strong IA and product storytelling in a collaborative setting Personal time management and priority juggling skills to hit evolving deadlines Eagle eyes and problem solving brain Online portfolio with relevant work you\u2019re proud of What will impress us even more: Illustration, iconography Motion graphics and/or CSS animation Experience building responsive emails InDesign knowledge Questions: Tell us why you\u2019re perfect for this role. Please provide a link to your portfolio, demonstrating your abilities and experience as a marketing web designer. Please provide links to at least 2 examples of live sites you\u2019ve designed and built on the HubSpot platform. Please provide a link to 1 email you\u2019ve designed and built on HubSpot. We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at Circle. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. ???????????????????????? Boston ", 
